name: Alarm Call
wikiSummary:
Released as a single in december 1998.  Due to the production-title "Jacko" as found on the Homogenic demo tape, it is rumored to be a song in tribute to the late Michael Jackson.  "I do believe in the power of music to change things. I do sometimes feel like I'm the only one left who believes that."
 - Record Collector, August 2002
wikiText:
Released as a single in december 1998.
 
 Due to the production-title "Jacko" as found on the Homogenic demo tape, it is rumored to be a song in tribute to the late Michael Jackson.
 
 "I do believe in the power of music to change things. I do sometimes feel like I'm the only one left who believes that."
 - Record Collector, August 2002
